      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While the primary issue with large datasets is holding the entire object, there can certainly be other memory leaks or high usage in the background. For instance, intermediate operations, complex Pandas manipulations, or inefficient data types can accumulate memory outside of the generator's output. It's always wise to profile your script using tools like `memory_profiler` to precisely locate which part of the process is consuming resources, just in case it's not strictly the size of the data being processed.",
      "source": "target",
